\f0\fs26 \cf0 The idea is essentially a 
\f1\b unified AML/KYC compliance platform
\f0\b0 . The important point is to understand that 
\f1\b KYC is only one component of the wider AML/CFT framework
\f0\b0 . This product combines several systems that are traditionally separated: customer onboarding, KYC/KYB, screening, risk assessment, transaction monitoring, case management, workflows and auditability. \
It is a 
\f1\b Compliance Operating System
\f0\b0 .\
\uc0\u8232 \
\
\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 . The complete AML/KYC lifecycle\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs26 \cf0 A financial institution needs to answer:\

\f1\b Who is this customer? What is their risk? Who controls them? What are they doing? Is anything suspicious? Can we prove why we made our decisions?
\f0\b0 \
ComplianceOS could centralize the entire lifecycle:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 CUSTOMER\
   \uc0\u8595 \
ONBOARDING\
   \uc0\u8595 \
IDENTITY / ENTITY VERIFICATION\
   \uc0\u8595 \
KYC / KYB DATA COLLECTION\
   \uc0\u8595 \
UBO & OWNERSHIP ANALYSIS\
   \uc0\u8595 \
SANCTIONS / PEP / ADVERSE MEDIA SCREENING\
   \uc0\u8595 \
RISK ASSESSMENT\
   \uc0\u8595 \
CDD / EDD\
   \uc0\u8595 \
ONGOING MONITORING\
   \uc0\u8595 \
TRANSACTION MONITORING\
   \uc0\u8595 \
ALERT\
   \uc0\u8595 \
INVESTIGATION / CASE MANAGEMENT\
   \uc0\u8595 \
DECISION\
   \uc0\u8595 \
AUDIT TRAIL / REPORTING\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26 \cf0 \uc0\u8232 \
\
\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 . The main modules compliance software would need\
A. Customer onboarding\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs26 \cf0 The customer could be:\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f3\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\fs26 an individual;\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f3\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\fs26 a company;\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f3\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\fs26 a trust;\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f3\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\fs26 a fund;\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f3\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\fs26 a financial institution;\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f3\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\fs26 another legal entity.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The onboarding module would collect:\

\f1\b Individual\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf0 First name\
Last name\
Date of birth\
Nationality\
Country of residence\
Address\
Occupation\
Tax residence\
ID document\
Source of funds\
Source of wealth\
Purpose of relationship\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs26 \cf0 Company\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf0 Legal name\
Registration number\
Country of incorporation\
Registered address\
Business activity\
Directors\
Shareholders\
UBOs\
Ownership percentages\
Source of funds\
Source of wealth\
Purpose of relationship\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26 \cf0 The key concept is that the system should not simply have a form.\
It should have a 
\f1\b dynamic questionnaire
\f0\b0 .\
For example:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 Customer = Company\
Country = Luxembourg\
Business = Crypto exchange\
UBO = PEP\
Country exposure = High-risk jurisdiction\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26 \cf0 The system should automatically determine:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 Required:\
\uc0\u10003  Corporate documents\
\uc0\u10003  UBO identification\
\uc0\u10003  PEP screening\
\uc0\u10003  Sanctions screening\
\uc0\u10003  Enhanced Due Diligence\
\uc0\u10003  Source of Wealth\
\uc0\u10003  Source of Funds\
\uc0\u10003  Senior management approval\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26 \cf0 This is one of the most important aspects of the platform.\

\f1\b The software should dynamically determine what compliance actions are required based on the customer\'92s profile.
\f0\b0 \
\uc0\u8232 \
\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 . KYC and KYB\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs26 \cf0 We separate these concepts:\

\f1\b KYC\
Know Your Customer
\f0\b0 \
Primarily concerns individuals.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 Is this person really who they claim to be?\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs26 \cf0 KYB\
Know Your Business
\f0\b0 \
Concerns companies.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 Does this company really exist?\
Who owns it?\
Who controls it?\
What does it actually do?\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26 \cf0 A business may have:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 Company A\
   \uc0\u8595  80%\
Company B\
   \uc0\u8595  70%\
Company C\
   \uc0\u8595  60%\
John Smith\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26 \cf0 Compliance iO platform must calculate the 
\f1\b Ultimate Beneficial Owner
\f0\b0 .\
That means you need a relationship graph:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0           John Smith\
              \uc0\u9474 \
           60%\
              \uc0\u9474 \
          Company C\
              \uc0\u9474 \
           70%\
              \uc0\u9474 \
          Company B\
              \uc0\u9474 \
           80%\
              \uc0\u9474 \
          Company A\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26 \cf0 This is a very important technical feature.\
I would model this using entities such as:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 User\
Company\
Person\
Ownership\
ControlRelationship\
Director\
BeneficialOwner\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26 \cf0 And visually display it as a graph.\
\uc0\u8232 \
\
\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 . Screening
\f0\b0\fs26 \
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 The platform should allow an analyst to search a customer against multiple sources.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 Sanctions\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs26 \cf0 For example:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 EU Sanctions\
UN Sanctions\
UK Sanctions\
US OFAC\
Other national lists\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26 \cf0 The output might be:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 John Smith\
    \uc0\u8595 \
Sanctions screening\
    \uc0\u8595 \
Potential match found\
    \uc0\u8595 \
Similarity: 87%\
    \uc0\u8595 \
Nationality: Unknown\
Date of birth: Unknown\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26 \cf0 The important thing is:\

\f1\b A name match is not automatically a true match.
\f0\b0 \
The analyst must compare:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 Name\
Date of birth\
Nationality\
Address\
Passport\
Company\
Known aliases\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26 \cf0 The system should allow:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 \uc0\u10003  Confirmed match\
\uc0\u10003  False positive\
\uc0\u10003  Requires further investigation\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26 \cf0 \uc0\u8232 \
\
\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 PEP screening\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs26 \cf0 A PEP is a:\

\f1\b Politically Exposed Person
\f0\b0 \
The platform should detect:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 Current PEP\
Former PEP\
Family member\
Close associate\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26 \cf0 This does not necessarily mean that the customer is committing a crime.\
It means that the customer generally requires 
\f1\b additional risk analysis
\f0\b0 .\
\uc0\u8232 \
\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 Adverse media\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs26 \cf0 The platform can search for negative information related to:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 Money laundering\
Fraud\
Corruption\
Terrorism financing\
Drug trafficking\
Organized crime\
Financial crime\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26 \cf0 This is where AI is particularly useful.\
For example:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 Customer:\
John Smith\
\
Articles found:\
1. "Former director investigated for corruption"\
2. "Company fined for regulatory violations"\
3. "Unrelated football player named John Smith"\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26 \cf0 The AI could classify:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 Article 1 \uc0\u8594  Relevant\
Article 2 \uc0\u8594  Relevant\
Article 3 \uc0\u8594  Irrelevant\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26 \cf0 But  
\f1\b AI  is not allow to make the final compliance decision
\f0\b0 .\
A better model is:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 AI = research assistant\
Human = final decision-maker\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26 \cf0 The platform preserves:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 What the AI found\
Which sources were used\
When they were found\
What the analyst decided\
Why the analyst decided it\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs26 \cf0 That creates an audit-ready process.\
\uc0\u8232 \

\f4 \uc0\u11835 
\f0 \
\uc0\u8232 \
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 . Risk scoring\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs26 \cf0 Every customer have a risk profile.\
For example:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 Customer Risk Score\
\uc0\u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \
